<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Historical Information
</head>
<p>Scott County was named for Winfield Scott, a native of Virginia, in recognition of his victories during the War of 1812. It was formed from Lee, Russell, and Washington counties in 1814.
</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>Scott County (Va.) Court Records, 1874-1914, consist of vital statistic records and military and pension records. The vital statistics records consist of registers of births (1874, 1876, 1800-1887, 1890-1891, 1895) and registers of deaths (1874, 1880, 1882-1887, 1890-1891). The military and pension records consist of Confederate pension applications (1902-1908, 1912-1914), a list of applicants for pensions on file in the office of the circuit court clerk (1902 July 1), and Board of Commissioners of Pension reports and lists (1902-1913).
</p>
</scopecontent>
